[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'It\'s time to meet and static, the open-source self-hostable static CMS with its own powerful page builder. It has content management tools, a secure plug-in system, a bring your own key AI integration, HTML and full-sight import,'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'and a lot more. One of the best parts is that it publishes static HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with dynamic holes in the style of Astro\'s dynamic islands,'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'enabling you to show content from the built-in database easily while still benefiting from the performance gains of static pages. Instatic is still in the pre-alpha phase, but we\'re excited to show you what we think an open-source'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'self-hostable static CMS should be. Let\'s take a closer look. Instatic is really built for the era of AI. Just plug in your own key from your preferred provider and you can start using AI right inside of Instatic. Use Anthropic,'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'OpenAI, or even local models via Olama. Or if you want a wider variety, use Open Router to access over 400 models. Within Instatic, you access the AI assistant'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'panel via either the AI button or the command or control plus I keyboard shortcut. Choose your model, then start working with the assistant to create or tweak color, size, and spacing tokens,'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'create pages, templates, or full structures, write content, or even help organize your media files. The visual builder is purpose-made for responsive design with the default view being a'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'multi-breakpoint canvas. See your desktop, tablet, and mobile breakpoints all at once and easily switch between them to tweak your designs. Or zoom into a specific breakpoint by switching to'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the live mode, so you can focus on the specific layout you need to adjust. You can see the entire page structure in the layers panel, neatly organized with visually distinct badges for each node'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'type. Drill down and select any node to access the visual design interface, giving you access to all of the CSS properties you need, as well as custom properties and even interactions. The class-based design system makes it easy'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'to create reusable designs that scale. And the selectors panel gives you the ability to manage all selectors, including a fast search input and an option to rename already created'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'selectors. Lock in your design system via the colors, typography, and spacing tabs. Use CSS variables to define your color system and static can autogenerate utility classes, shades, and tints for'

[02:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'each color on an as needed basis. Add Google fonts or upload your own and create powerful typography scales for consistent text sizes. Create reusable spacing scales in the spacing panel,'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'which provides a friendly interface for creating versatile spacing variables and utility classes for use throughout your designs. These panels are your visual interface for creating and maintaining your complete design system, ensuring'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the changes you need to make later are easy and fast. And static also includes full user and role management. see access levels, last login, create and manage users from the users tab. Under'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'users roles, you can see and manage existing roles as well as creating new ones. Ro capabilities are highly granular as well. For example, the built-in client role can see the site'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'design and edit text content, but can\'t drag and drop, restructure, or make other more drastic changes to the site. Plus, you can keep an eye on the actions users perform under the users audit tab. This makes Instatic the perfect CMS for'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'client handoff on sites you\'re still managing, ensuring you can give clients and other stakeholders the control they need while keeping more technical or sensitive capabilities locked down. Many'

[03:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'new static CMS offerings lack the extensibility that makes other CMS\'s like WordPress so adaptable. Instatic comes out of the gate with plugins as a firstclass feature, but done in the'

[04:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'modern secure way. The developer SDK gives devs a clear API to communicate with the CMS through the boundaries of the built-in permission system. The user will clearly see what level of access'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'each plugin has and which external URLs are whitelisted if they\'re required for the plugin to work. This limits the surface area that plugins have access to. Ensuring you\'re in static site'

[04:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'remains secure, even if you need extra functionality. Building from scratch in a new interface can be intimidating. And even though in statics interface is basically a guey for HTML and CSS, it\'s much faster to kickstart your project'

[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'with a template or at least a base design. That\'s where the site import and HTML import options really save the day. First, let\'s talk about site import. You can drop in a site folder with all of'

[04:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'your HTML, CSS, images, and fonts, and Instatic will process the files. It then splits everything into Instatic nodes, selectors, files, and design tokens. You can then edit the imported site using'

[05:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'the Instatic interface. But if you want to import something a bit simpler, like a single HTML section or component, the HTML import option is perfect. Paste the HTML and static will process it into'

[05:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'nodes for the builder and you\'re done. Deploying your very own Instatic instance couldn\'t be simpler. Use the one-click deployment links in our GitHub to deploy to Railway in minutes using either SQL light or Postgress as your'

[05:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'database. If you prefer to deploy somewhere else, Instatic has a convenient Docker image and thorough documentation to help you deploy to Railway Render, a self-hosted VPS via'

[05:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Docker Compose, and any platform capable of running the Docker file and image. We made static fully open- source, MIT licensed, and completely free to use.'

[05:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'The code\'s all on GitHub and were open to thirdparty contributors as well. So, if you want to not only use Instatic for free, but help shape how it grows, you can do that. And we\'d love to see what'

[06:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'you come up with. There\'s still so much we want to do with Instatic. So, we\'re excited to see the feedback that we receive from users like you. But here are a few of the things already on our road map. The UI is moving in the right'

[06:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'direction, but we want to polish it even more to make it easy to use and remove a few points of friction. We\'re going to quickly expand our library of content to help users get up to speed faster. We plan to start building some firstparty'

[06:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'plugins, modules, and integrations to extend in static beyond the basics and lots more that we\'re not quite ready to talk about yet. Follow along on GitHub and don\'t forget to start the project by clicking the star icon near the top'

[06:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'right. If you\'re excited to come on this journey with us, you can learn more at instatic.com.'
